  "local_port": 57304,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I uninstall Modified apk by Lucky Patcher (I can only deactivate it)?",
  "response": "Uninstalling a modified APK created with Lucky Patcher can be straightforward. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to uninstall it:\n\n1. **Deactivate the App:**\n   - If you have only deactivated the app and haven't done a full uninstall yet, you can start by going to your device's **Settings**.\n   - Navigate to **Apps** (or **Applications** depending on your device).\n   - Find the modified APK in the list of applications and tap on it.\n   - If there is an option to \"Deactivate\" or \"Disable,\" you can choose that. This will stop the app from running, but it doesn\u2019t uninstall it.\n\n2. **Uninstall the App:**\n   - Still in the **Apps** section, look for the modified APK you want to uninstall.\n   - Select the app, and you should see an **Uninstall** button.\n   - Tap on **Uninstall** to remove the app from your device. Confirm any prompts that appear.\n\n3. **Using Lucky Patcher (if necessary):**\n   - If you find the app is still active or you cannot uninstall it from the settings, open Lucky Patcher.\n   - Find the modified app within Lucky Patcher's interface.\n   - Tap on the app and look for an option to \"Uninstall.\" This will help you remove the app effectively.\n\n4. **Clear Cache and Data (optional but recommended):**\n   - Before uninstalling, you may want to clear the app's cache and data. This can help avoid any residual files being left behind.\n   - Go to the app in your device's settings, and select **Storage**. From there, you can clear cache and data before proceeding with the uninstall.\n\n5. **Reboot Your Device:**\n   - After uninstalling the app, it\u2019s good practice to restart your device. This helps in clearing any temporary files and ensuring all components related to the app are removed.\n\n6. **Check for Leftover Files:**\n   - Sometimes, modded APKs might leave behind residual files or folders. You can use a file manager app to check your device\u2019s storage and clean any leftovers if necessary.\n\nIf you follow these steps, you should be able to fully uninstall the modified APK from your Android device.",
